1- Pylint - is a quality checker of Python Programming Language.
2- It follows the style recommended by PEP 8, the Python style guide  (https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/)
3- It can be used as a stand-alone program, but also integrates with IDEs 
4- sudo apt-get install pylint (to install in Ubunutu)
5- We can run this (when we want to perform some automated tests) - to check if code is matching some coding standards

Pylinter basically inspect our python code, and gives the feedback based on PEP8 coding standards